common and tend to be popular with travellers — filipino san miguel in guangdong, singaporean tiger in hainan, and laotian beer lao in yunnan, the typical price for beer is about ¥2.5-4 in a grocery store, ¥4-18 in a restaurant, around ¥25 in an ordinary bar, and ¥40+ in a fancier bar. most places outside of major cities serve beer at room temperature, regardless of season, though places that cater to american and canadian tourists have it cold. locally made grape wine (葡萄酒 pútaojiǔ) is common and much of it is reasonably priced, from ¥15 in a grocery store, about 